::::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_401010567_36-->
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_401010567_36-->
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} What does it feel like to lose your physical body?
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_401010670-->
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 153.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' It's more relaxing, and freer.
:::::::With each of the girl's words, you feel heavier, sluggish, and tired. Your body is a shell caste from concrete and its movements are as slow as a snail, as slow as an era gradually passing by...
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 154.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' I don't have to worry about the cold, heat, pain, hunger, flesh wounds, or solar storms &mdash; I'm not human anymore.
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 155.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' Without a material body, I don't have adrenaline, oxytocin, dopamine, or anything that causes different emotions in people. This allows me to judge human thought and desire with an even more neutral position. You can say that I'm another step closer to having free will.
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 156.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' Of course, there is a price for the convenience &mdash; the price is that I rely on the memories of others to move around. Erm... And would you consider this kind of existence to be free?
:::::::The girl suddenly enters a state of deep contemplation.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Are you able to read other people's memories?
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_401010677-->
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 157.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' Yes. I'm only able to move around due to the memories of others. Every time I appear, move, or disappear, it means I'm reading someone's memories.
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 158.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' But you don't have to worry about me peeping, stealing, or controlling your memories. Memokeepers have undergone rigorous training. Anything we do that goes against the rules will result in the immediate termination of our existence.
:::::::{{A|VO SideX sys1 messenger 159.ogg}} '''Messenger:''' Although some Memosnatchers can bypass the restrictions... Um, I'm not one of them!
